                        },
                        "description": "<p>To collect animals for metabolite extraction, animals were gently washed off the plates (wells) using ice-cold M9 supplemented with 0.01% (v/v) Triton X-100 and transferred to a 15 mL tube. Subsequently, the animals were washed 4 times with 10 mL of ice-cold M9 containing 0.01% Triton X-100 to remove bacteria and eggs. During each wash, the tube was first vortexed for ~5 s and then allowed to stand on ice for approximately 2 min, to settle adult animals to the bottom of the tubes (forming a ~800 \u00b5L pellet of animals), while bacteria and most eggs remained in the supernatant. Following this, 800 \u00b5L of the animal pellet was transferred to a well of an ice-cold 96-well filter plate (Enzymax: EZ96FTP). The plate was then centrifuged at 4 \u00b0C and 1400 x g for 30 s and washed 4 times with 800 \u00b5L of ice-cold 0.9% NaCl solution, each time followed by centrifugation.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "",
                                    "termSource": null,
