                                }
                            }
                        ],
                        "components": []
                    },
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Extraction",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Extraction",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>For gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS) samples, the final animal pellet was resuspended in 500 \u00b5L ice-cold 80% methanol. The resuspended samples were transferred to 2 mL FastPrep tubes pre-filled with 0.5 mL acid-washed glass beads (G1277, Sigma). For each sample, the resuspension step was repeated for another time to transfer residual animals to the same 2 mL tube.&nbsp;Homogenization was achieved using a FastPrep 24 at 6 m/s for 1 min, repeated 3 times with a 3-min interval, allowing samples to chill on ice. The homogenized samples were then transferred to 1.5 mL Eppendorf tubes without glass beads, followed by centrifugation at top speed (4 \u00b0C, ~15,000 x g) for 10 min to separate precipitates. For each sample, the supernatant (~ 800 \u00b5L) was carefully transferred to a new 1.5 mL Eppendorf tube, and the pellet was resuspended in 1 mL of RIPA buffer for protein concentration measurement using the BCA Protein Assay.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
