                            "annotationValue": "Chromatography",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>GC-MS was conducted using an Agilent 7890B single quadrupole mass spectrometer, coupled with an Agilent 5977B gas chromatograph equipped with an HP-5MS Ultra Inert capillary column (30 m, 0.25 mm x 0.25 \u03bcm). Operating parameters were set as follows: the inlet temperature was maintained at 230 \u00b0C, the transfer line at 280 \u00b0C, and both the mass spectrometer source and quadrupole were maintained at temperatures of 230 and 150 \u00b0C, respectively. In total 1 \u00b5L of derivatization product was injected to inlet with splitless mode. We used two distinct running methods, characterized by variations in the oven temperature program, to facilitate the detection of diverse metabolites. Method 1 involved programming the oven to initiate at 80 \u00b0C, maintaining this temperature for 2 min, and then ramping it up at a rate of 5 \u00b0C/min until reaching 280 \u00b0C. Method 2 used an initial oven temperature of 130 \u00b0C, held for 1 min, followed by a ramp-up at 5 \u00b0C/min until reaching 325 \u00b0C. In the metabolite list, a metabolite name ending with '(method1)' or '(method2)' indicates it was run using Method 1 or Method 2, respectively. The sample sheets also provide the running method information for each sample.</p>",
